author: Mike DuPont
title: Kingsbury: Tech OL Justin Murphy needs surgery, is out for season
text:
Texas Tech right guard Justin Murphy is out for the season and preparing for knee surgery head coach Kliff Kingsbury told various media outlets following Tuesday's practice.
Kliff Kingsbury said after today's practice that OL Justin Murphy will miss the rest of the season due to a knee injury. #TexasTech
â€” RedRaiderSports.com (@RedRaiderSports) October 13, 2015 The 6-foot-6, 298-pound redshirt freshman was injured in an Oct. 3 game against Baylor. Murphy started the second the second through fifth games at right guard.
In those five games, the Red Raiders rushed for a combined 721 yards and 14 touchdowns.
Tony Morales was chosen to start against Iowa State in his absence. The twin brother of starting center Alfredo Morales also started the season-opener against Sam Houston State.
"Still a little rusty, but I love the effort he plays with, both those brothers really play with incredible effort" Kingsbury said during his Monday press conference. "They really push each other so for not having played in a game for however long, he's come a long way."
"One thing, when you turn on the tape - he's going to play as hard as he can and run as fast as he can every snap."
